# Finch Brand

- **Tagline**: "Fewer Applications. More Interviews."
- **Hero headline**: "Turn Applications Into Interviews."
- **Tone**: Playful, Innovative, Approachable (Duolingo-inspired energy)
- **Audience**: 19-23 year old CS/Engineering undergrads applying for internships

## Colors
- Navy: #1c3249 (primary dark)
- Red: #ed1c24 (primary accent)
- Orange: #f7941d (secondary accent)
- Finch Orange: #E8401C (warm accent)
- Green: #58CC02 (success/positive, Duolingo-inspired)
- White: #ffffff
- Logo uses a gradient from navy through red to orange

## Typography
- Primary: Nunito (Google Fonts, rounded sans-serif matching logo energy)
- Fallback: system-ui, sans-serif
- Never: Times New Roman, Arial, Inter as primary

## Logo
- Bird-shaped "f" lettermark with parrot beak detail
- Available in: gradient (orange), dark (red-orange), light background variant
- The "f" icon can be used standalone as a favicon/badge

## Product Context
- Chrome extension for internship applications
- AI-powered resume tailoring + autofill on Greenhouse, Lever, Workday
- Reduces 20-30 min application to under 60 seconds
- Not an auto-apply tool — intentional, response-optimization platform
- Reference: applyfinch.com for existing product UI patterns
